    * _e
In _c_r_i_m_i_n_a_l_ _l_a_w, ffrraauudd is _i_n_t_e_n_t_i_o_n_a_l _d_e_c_e_p_t_i_o_n made for personal gain or to
damage another individual; the related adjective is ffrraauudduulleenntt, and verb is
ddeeffrraauudd. Fraud is a _c_r_i_m_e and a _c_i_v_i_l _t_o_r_t at common law, though the specific
_c_r_i_m_i_n_a_l_ _l_a_w definition varies by _l_e_g_a_l_ _j_u_r_i_s_d_i_c_t_i_o_n. Defrauding people or
entities of _m_o_n_e_y or valuables is a common purpose of fraud.
A _h_o_a_x also involves deception, but without the intention of gain or of
damaging or depriving the victim. Fraud is a _d_e_f_e_n_s_e in a _c_i_v_i_l_ _a_c_t_i_o_n for
_b_r_e_a_c_h_ _o_f_ _c_o_n_t_r_a_c_t or _s_p_e_c_i_f_i_c_ _p_e_r_f_o_r_m_a_n_c_e of a _c_o_n_t_r_a_c_t. Fraud is a basis for
_e_q_u_i_t_a_b_l_e_ _j_u_r_i_s_d_i_c_t_i_o_n.
********** CCoonntteennttss **********
